    "summary": "Shopify publicly documents GraphQL Admin, legacy REST Admin, Storefront, Customer Account, Payments Apps, webhooks, and specialized APIs for products, customers, orders, inventory, checkout, and store operations.",
    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Shopify Admin APIs. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Shopify's public API hub organizes the platform around GraphQL Admin API, legacy REST Admin API, Storefront API, Customer Account API, Payments Apps API, webhooks, and app events. Public descriptions state that these APIs let integrators read and write products, customers, orders, inventory, checkouts, payments, and buyer-facing storefront data, while reacting to store changes in real time through webhook events. Shopify also exposes customer privacy, customer identity, partner, and storefront surfaces for headless and embedded commerce scenarios. This is a write-capable retail commerce platform, but it does not represent asset or telemetry data. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
